        "heading": "Hedonist at heart",
        "heading_font": "'Manrope', sans-serif",
        "heading_size": 32,
        "heading_weight": "400",
        "heading_color": "#030303",
        "text": "<p>Finding meaning in poetry, art and the architecture of aesthetics. </p><p>Certain flowers releasing their intoxicating scent at night. Soil becoming alive after rain. That electric tension between harmony and chaos, beauty and rot - is what infuses matter with soul. Fragrance should do the same. </p><p>To smell like everyone else is to disappear. </p><p>As a curator for soul of scents, my role is dedicated to translating the unseen into something you can wear, something you can truly make yours. </p><p>With a decade of experience training my nose to pick up subtle nuances and notes, I present only compositions of exceptional craftsmanship and depth. Scents that don’t just sit on you but merge with you.</p><p>Every fragrance you encounter here has been meticulously selected for its ability to spark recognition, start conversation, or shape your most intimate moments. </p><p>Scent is expressing your identity, and that I take very seriously.</p>",
